    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix misleading comment in AuthenticationFailure decoder causing developer confusion\n\n### Summary\nThe `decode_authentication_failure` function in `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/AuthenticationFailure.c` contained a misleading comment that incorrectly described when IEI masking occurs. The comment stated \"Type | value iei are below 0x80 so just return the first 4 bits\" but the actual code applied masking for IEIs >= 0x80. This inconsistency could confuse developers maintaining the code and potentially lead to incorrect modifications.\n\nThis fix corrects the comment to accurately reflect the code's behavior.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/AuthenticationFailure.c`: Updated misleading comment to correctly describe IEI processing logic.\n\n### Reproduction\nDevelopers reading the code to understand IEI handling would incorrectly believe that masking applies to IEIs below 0x80, when actually it applies to IEIs >= 0x80. This could lead to incorrect assumptions when extending the decoder or debugging related issues.\n\n"
}